This paper deals with the problem of inconsistency in databases, which is a core topic in database theory (cs.DB). However, the proposed framework incorporates statistical reasoning and probabilistic models, which are also central to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses computational problems related to probabilistic query answering and learning, which are relevant to data science (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT).
